{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775851522202,"sessionID":"ses_287007af5ffe4FwON8tsyu2Ogd","part":{"id":"prt_d78ffbaeb001AVfE7RO7E7VNKf","messageID":"msg_d78ffacd5001xeKarB6UUKKxdR","sessionID":"ses_287007af5ffe4FwON8tsyu2Ogd","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_ef3e45b92e7249b7a777ab61","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/session-store/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/session-store/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Session Store — Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Attribute | Value |\n6: |-----------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-012 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/store` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | S |\n11: \n12: ## Related Components\n13: \n14: The session store integrates with the Kubernetes client library (`client-go`) which provides typed clients for the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group. The client-go library supports `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` CRDs for sandbox orchestration. Session metadata may reference these K8s resources via the `runtime.agentcube` clientset.\n15: \n16: See `deployment/client-go.md` for full client-go library specification.\n17: \n18: ## Module\n19: \n20: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` — versions in sandbox-orchestration `design.md`.\n21: \n22: ## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store`\n23: \n24: ### Store interface (exact signatures)\n25: \n26: ```go\n27: package store\n28: \n29: import (\n30:     \"context\"\n31:     \"time\"\n32: \n33:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n34: )\n35: \n36: type Store interface {\n37:     Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n38:     GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n39:     StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n40:     UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n41:     DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n42:     ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n43:     ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n44:     UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n45:     Close() error\n46: }\n47: ```\n48: \n49: ### Errors\n50: \n51: ```go\n52: var ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n53: ```\n54: \n55: ### Provider type constants (`singleton.go`)\n56: \n57: ```go\n58: const (\n59:     redisStoreType  string = \"redis\"\n60:     valkeyStoreType string = \"valkey\"\n61: )\n62: ```\n63: \n64: ### Singleton\n65: \n66: ```go\n67: var (\n68:     initStoreOnce = &sync.Once{}\n69:     provider      Store\n70: )\n71: \n72: func Storage() Store\n73: func initStore() error\n74: ```\n75: \n76: - `Storage()` calls `initStoreOnce.Do(initStore)`; on error `klog.Fatalf(\"init store failed: %v\", err)`.\n77: \n78: ### Sandbox document type\n79: \n80: Stored JSON unmarshals to `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types.SandboxInfo`:\n81: \n82: ```go\n83: type SandboxInfo struct {\n84:     Kind             string              `json:\"kind\"`\n85:     SandboxID        string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n86:     SandboxNamespace string              `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n87:     Name             string              `json:\"name\"`\n88:     EntryPoints      []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n89:     SessionID        string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n90:     CreatedAt        time.Time           `json:\"createdAt\"`\n91:     ExpiresAt        time.Time           `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n92:     Status           string              `json:\"status\"`\n93: }\n94: \n95: type SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n96:     Path     string `json:\"path\"`\n97:     Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n98:     Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n99: }\n100: ```\n101: \n102: ## Redis implementation (`store_redis.go`)\n103: \n104: ### Struct\n105: \n106: ```go\n107: type redisStore struct {\n108:     cli                  *redisv9.Client  // github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\n109:     sessionPrefix        string\n110:     expiryIndexKey       string\n111:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n112: }\n113: ```\n114: \n115: ### Fixed key patterns\n116: \n117: | Field | Value |\n118: |-------|--------|\n119: | `sessionPrefix` | `\"session:\"` |\n120: | `expiryIndexKey` | `\"session:expiry\"` |\n121: | `lastActivityIndexKey` | `\"session:last_activity\"` |\n122: \n123: ### Connection options (`makeRedisOptions`)\n124: \n125: ```go\n126: return &redisv9.Options{\n127:     Addr:     redisAddr,     // REDIS_ADDR\n128:     Password: redisPassword, // REDIS_PASSWORD\n129: }, nil\n130: ```\n131: \n132: ### Environment variables (Redis)\n133: \n134: | Variable | Required | Notes |\n135: |----------|----------|--------|\n136: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes | |\n137: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Yes unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` | Case-insensitive compare to `\"false\"` |\n138: | `STORE_TYPE` | No | Default `redis` |\n139: \n140: ### Operations summary\n141: \n142: | Method | Redis commands |\n143: |--------|----------------|\n144: | `Ping` | `PING` → expect `PONG` |\n145: | `GetSandboxBySessionID` | `GET session:{id}` |\n146: | `StoreSandbox` | Pipeline: `SETNX`, `ZADD session:expiry`, `ZADD session:last_activity` |\n147: | `UpdateSandbox` | `SET key value XX` |\n148: | `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | Pipeline: `DEL`, `ZREM expiry`, `ZREM last_activity` |\n149: | `ListExpiredSandboxes` | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix} LIMIT 0 limit` then pipeline GETs |\n150: | `ListInactiveSandboxes` | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity ...` then pipeline GETs |\n151: | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` | `GET` (existence), then `ZADD session:last_activity` |\n152: | `Close` | `cli.Close()` |\n153: \n154: - `List*` with `limit <= 0` returns `nil, nil`.\n155: - `sessionKey(id)` → `sessionPrefix + sessionID`.\n156: \n157: ## Valkey implementation (`store_valkey.go`)\n158: \n159: ### Struct\n160: \n161: ```go\n162: type valkeyStore struct {\n163:     cli                  valkey.Client  // github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\n164:     sessionPrefix        string\n165:     expiryIndexKey       string\n166:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n167: }\n168: ```\n169: \n170: Same string constants as Redis for prefix and ZSET keys.\n171: \n172: ### Connection options (`makeValkeyOptions`)\n173: \n174: ```go\n175: valkeyClientOptions := &valkey.ClientOption{\n176:     InitAddress: strings.Split(valkeyAddr, \",\"),\n177:     Password:    valkeyPassword,\n178: }\n179: ```\n180: \n181: Optional: `DisableCache` from `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` (ParseBool, must be true); `ForceSingleClient` from `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` (ParseBool, must be true).\n182: \n183: ### Environment variables (Valkey)\n184: \n185: | Variable | Required | Notes |\n186: |----------|----------|--------|\n187: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | Comma-separated list → `InitAddress` |\n188: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` | |\n189: | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `\"true\"` enables `DisableCache` |\n190: | `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `\"true\"` enables `ForceSingleClient` |\n191: | `STORE_TYPE` | Must be `valkey` | Case-insensitive |\n192: \n193: ### Operations summary\n194: \n195: | Method | Valkey API |\n196: |--------|------------|\n197: | `Ping` | `B().Ping()` → string `PONG` |\n198: | `GetSandboxBySessionID` | `B().Get().Key(key)` → bytes; `IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound` |\n199: | `StoreSandbox` | `DoMulti`: `SETNX`, `ZADD` expiry, `ZADD` last_activity |\n200: | `UpdateSandbox` | `SET ... XX`; success requires `ToString() == \"OK\"` |\n201: | `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | `DoMulti`: `DEL`, `ZREM` expiry, `ZREM` last_activity |\n202: | `ListExpiredSandboxes` | `Zrangebyscore` with `Min(\"-inf\")`, `Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix()))`, `Limit(0, limit)` |\n203: | `ListInactiveSandboxes` | Same on `last_activity` key |\n204: | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` | `Exists` key → int64 must be 1; then `Zadd` |\n205: | `Close` | `vs.cli.Close()` then return nil |\n206: \n207: ### ZSET score semantics\n208: \n209: - **Expiry index:** score = `float64(sandboxRedis.ExpiresAt.Unix())` on store.\n210: - **Last activity:** score = `float64(time.Now().Unix())` on `StoreSandbox`; `float64(at.Unix())` on `UpdateSessionLastActivity`.\n211: \n212: ### MGET note (Valkey)\n213: \n214: - `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` builds all `session:{id}` keys and uses single `Mget`; comment states keys should be in same slot (deployment consideration).\n215: \n216: ## Dependencies (store package imports)\n217: \n218: - `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9`\n219: - `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`\n220: - `k8s.io/klog/v2` (Valkey options logging)\n221: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types`\n222: \n223: ## Architecture\n224: \n225: ### Overview\n226: \n227: The Session Store module provides a unified interface for persisting sandbox metadata with support for both Redis and Valkey backends. The design follows the provider pattern, allowing runtime selection of the underlying storage backend through configuration.\n228: \n229: ```\n230: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n231: │                    pkg/store                            │\n232: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n233: │  ┌─────────────┐    ┌─────────────┐    ┌─────────────┐  │\n234: │  │   Store     │    │ redisStore  │    │ valkeyStore │  │\n235: │  │  Interface  │◄───│  (Redis 9)  │    │ (Valkey)    │  │\n236: │  └─────────────┘    └─────────────┘    └─────────────┘  │\n237: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n238: │  Singleton: Storage() → Store                           │\n239: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n240: │  Data Model: Session ID → SandboxInfo (JSON)           │\n241: │  Index 1: session:expiry (ZSET) → sessionID:expireTS   │\n242: │  Index 2: session:last_activity (ZSET) → sessionID:ts  │\n243: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n244: ```\n245: \n246: ### Data Flow\n247: \n248: 1. **Store Operations**: All write operations update both the session document and the two ZSET indexes atomically via pipeline/multi commands.\n249: 2. **List Operations**: Query ZSET for session IDs, then batch-fetch documents.\n250: 3. **GC Operations**: ListExpiredSandboxes and ListInactiveSandboxes support garbage collection of stale sessions.\n251: \n252: ## Error Handling\n253: \n254: ### Error Types\n255: \n256: | Error | Condition | Return Value |\n257: |-------|-----------|--------------|\n258: | `ErrNotFound` | Session key missing | `errors.New(\"store: not found\")` |\n259: | Validation errors | Nil sandbox, zero ExpiresAt | Context-specific messages |\n260: | Connection errors | Redis/Valkey unreachable | Propagated from client |\n261: \n262: ### Error Recovery\n263: \n264: - **Get operations**: Return `ErrNotFound` for missing keys, propagate other errors.\n265: - **Write operations**: Pipeline failures abort the entire operation; partial writes do not occur.\n266: - **List operations**: Tolerate missing document keys for orphaned ZSET members.\n267: \n268: ### Logging\n269: \n270: - Initialization failures log via `klog.Fatalf`.\n271: - Valkey optional flags logged at info level during option building.\n272: \n273: ## Testing Strategy\n274: \n275: ### Unit Tests\n276: \n277: | File | Coverage |\n278: |------|----------|\n279: | `store_redis_test.go` | Redis store implementation |\n280: | `store_valkey_test.go` | Valkey store implementation |\n281: | `singleton_test.go` | Singleton initialization |\n282: \n283: ### Test Approach\n284: \n285: - **Mock strategy**: Use interfaces for Redis/Valkey clients to enable mock-based testing.\n286: - **Test fixtures**: Predefined `SandboxInfo` objects for CRUD test cases.\n287: - **Integration tests**: Point to test Redis/Valkey instances via environment variables.\n288: \n289: ### Key Test Scenarios\n290: \n291: 1. **Ping**: Verify connectivity returns PONG.\n292: 2. **CRUD cycle**: Store → Get → Update → Delete.\n293: 3. **Not found**: Get/Update/Delete on missing session returns `ErrNotFound`.\n294: 4. **List queries**: Verify ZSET-based listing returns correct sessions.\n295: 5. **Atomicity**: Pipeline failures leave no partial state.\n296: 6. **Singleton**: Concurrent Storage() calls initialize exactly once.\n297: \n298: ## File Structure\n299: \n300: ```\n301: pkg/store/\n302: ├── design.md           # This file\n303: ├── singleton.go        # Storage(), initStore()\n304: ├── store.go            # Store interface definition\n305: ├── errors.go           # ErrNotFound definition\n306: ├── store_redis.go      # Redis implementation\n307: ├── store_valkey.go     # Valkey implementation\n308: ├── store_redis_test.go # Redis tests\n309: ├── store_valkey_test.go# Valkey tests\n310: └── singleton_test.go   # Singleton tests\n311: ```\n\n(End of file - total 311 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Session Store — Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Attribute | Value |\n|-----------|-------|\n| AR | AR-012 |\n| Module | `pkg/store` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n\n## Related Components\n\nThe session store integrates with the Kubernetes client library (`client-go`) which provides typed clients for the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group. The client-go library supports `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` CRDs for sandbox orchestration. Session metadata may reference these K8s resources via the `runtime.agentcube` clientset.\n\nSee `deployment/client-go.md` for full client-go library specification.\n\n## Module\n\n- `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` — versions in sandbox-orchestration `design.md`.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/session-store/design.md","time":{"start":1775851522194,"end":1775851522200}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775851522240,"sessionID":"ses_287007af5ffe4FwON8tsyu2Ogd","part":{"id":"prt_d78ffbfa2001wsme3x49qRZ2Tj","messageID":"msg_d78ffacd5001xeKarB6UUKKxdR","sessionID":"ses_287007af5ffe4FwON8tsyu2Ogd","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_2afa2d85459d46d99948034a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/session-store/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/session-store/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Session Store Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Persist sandbox metadata keyed by session id, index sessions by expiry and last activity for garbage collection, and support Redis or Valkey backends selected by configuration.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Store interface contract\n9: The system SHALL provide a `Store` interface implemented by Redis and Valkey providers with methods: `Ping`, `GetSandboxBySessionID`, `StoreSandbox`, `UpdateSandbox`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`, `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes`, `UpdateSessionLastActivity`, and `Close`.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Ping verifies connectivity\n12: - **GIVEN** a healthy Redis/Valkey server\n13: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n14: - **THEN** the implementation issues PING and requires string response `PONG`\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Not found semantics\n17: The system SHALL return package error `ErrNotFound` (message `store: not found`) when a session key is absent on read or when last-activity update targets a missing session.\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Get missing session\n20: - **GIVEN** no key `session:{id}` in backend\n21: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID` runs\n22: - **THEN** error is `ErrNotFound` (Redis: `Nil`; Valkey: `IsValkeyNil`)\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Session key naming\n25: The system SHALL use string prefix `session:` concatenated with the session id as the primary key for JSON document storage.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Key construction\n28: - **GIVEN** session id `abc`\n29: - **WHEN** the store writes sandbox data\n30: - **THEN** the string key is `session:abc`\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Expiry index\n33: The system SHALL maintain sorted set key `session:expiry` with member = session id and score = `ExpiresAt` Unix seconds. `StoreSandbox` SHALL add the member with the sandbox expiry score. `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` SHALL remove the member.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: List expired uses ZRANGEBYSCORE\n36: - **GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` with limit > 0\n37: - **WHEN** the implementation queries the index\n38: - **THEN** it selects members with scores from negative infinity through `before.Unix()`, limited to `limit` entries\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: Last-activity index\n41: The system SHALL maintain sorted set key `session:last_activity` with member = session id and score = last activity Unix seconds. `StoreSandbox` SHALL ZADD with score `time.Now().Unix()` on initial store. `UpdateSessionLastActivity` SHALL ZADD with the provided timestamp (or now if zero). `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` SHALL ZREM the member.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: List inactive uses activity index\n44: - **GIVEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)`\n45: - **WHEN** executed\n46: - **THEN** members with last-activity score ≤ `before.Unix()` are returned up to `limit`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: StoreSandbox atomicity and validation\n49: The system SHALL reject nil sandbox or zero `ExpiresAt`. The system SHALL execute SETNX on session key, ZADD expiry, and ZADD last_activity in one pipeline/multi block. The system SHALL fail if any command in the batch errors.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Nil sandbox rejected\n52: - **GIVEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)`\n53: - **WHEN** called\n54: - **THEN** error indicates sandbox is nil\n55: \n56: ### Requirement: UpdateSandbox semantics\n57: The system SHALL update only the session JSON value using SET with XX (key must exist). The system SHALL NOT modify expiry or last-activity ZSET entries in this operation.\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: Missing key on update\n60: - **GIVEN** session key does not exist\n61: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` runs\n62: - **THEN** Redis: SETXX returns false → error `key not exists`; Valkey: response not OK → same error class\n63: \n64: ### Requirement: DeleteSandboxBySessionID cleanup\n65: The system SHALL delete session key and remove session id from both sorted sets in one pipeline/multi.\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Full removal\n68: - **GIVEN** an existing session\n69: - **WHEN** delete succeeds\n70: - **THEN** GET session key returns not found and ZSETs no longer contain the member\n71: \n72: ### Requirement: List loaders tolerate missing keys\n73: When listing by ZSET returns session ids, the system SHALL load JSON per id; SHALL skip entries where the string key is missing (Redis pipeline GET nil, Valkey MGET empty string) without failing the whole batch.\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Orphan ZSET member\n76: - **GIVEN** a session id in ZSET without a hash/string value\n77: - **WHEN** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` runs\n78: - **THEN** that id is omitted from the returned slice\n79: \n80: ### Requirement: UpdateSessionLastActivity preconditions\n81: The system SHALL reject empty session id. If `at` is zero time, the system SHALL use `time.Now()`. The system SHALL verify the session key exists before ZADD; if absent, SHALL return `ErrNotFound`.\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Activity bump for unknown session\n84: - **GIVEN** no `session:{id}` key\n85: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called\n86: - **THEN** return `ErrNotFound`\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Provider selection via STORE_TYPE\n89: The system SHALL read `STORE_TYPE` case-insensitively; if unset, SHALL default to `redis`. Supported values SHALL be `redis` and `valkey`; any other value SHALL fail initialization.\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Default redis\n92: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is not set\n93: - **WHEN** `Storage()` first initializes\n94: - **THEN** Redis implementation is constructed\n95: \n96: ### Requirement: Redis environment and password policy\n97: The system SHALL require `REDIS_ADDR`. The system SHALL require non-empty `REDIS_PASSWORD` unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `false`.\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: Password required by default\n100: - **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` set and `REDIS_PASSWORD` empty and `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` unset\n101: - **WHEN** Redis store initializes\n102: - **THEN** initialization fails with error stating password required\n103: \n104: ### Requirement: Valkey environment and options\n105: The system SHALL require `VALKEY_ADDR` (comma-separated addresses split for `InitAddress`). The system SHALL require non-empty `VALKEY_PASSWORD` unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`. The system SHALL set `DisableCache` true when `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` parses as true; SHALL set `ForceSingleClient` true when `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` parses as true.\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Optional client flags\n108: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true`\n109: - **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n110: - **THEN** `DisableCache` is true on `ClientOption`\n111: \n112: ### Requirement: Singleton access\n113: The system SHALL expose `func Storage() Store` using `sync.Once`; failed init SHALL log fatal via klog.\n114: \n115: #### Scenario: Single initialization\n116: - **GIVEN** multiple goroutines call `Storage()`\n117: - **WHEN** they run concurrently\n118: - **THEN** `initStore` executes exactly once\n\n(End of file - total 118 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Session Store Specification\n\n## Purpose\nPersist sandbox metadata keyed by session id, index sessions by expiry and last activity for garbage collection, and support Redis or Valkey backends selected by configuration.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Store interface contract\nThe system SHALL provide a `Store` interface implemented by Redis and Valkey providers with methods: `Ping`, `GetSandboxBySessionID`, `StoreSandbox`, `UpdateSandbox`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`, `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes`, `UpdateSessionLastActivity`, and `Close`.\n\n#### Scenario: Ping verifies connectivity\n- **GIVEN** a healthy Redis/Valkey server\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation issues PING and requires string response `PONG`\n\n### Requirement: Not found semantics\nThe system SHALL return package error `ErrNotFound` (message `store: not found`) when a session key is absent on read or when last-activity update targets a missing session.\n\n#### Scenario: Get missing session\n- **GIVEN** no key `session:{id}` in backend","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/session-store/spec.md","time":{"start":1775851522229,"end":1775851522238}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775851522252,"sessionID":"ses_287007af5ffe4FwON8tsyu2Ogd","part":{"id":"prt_d78ffc41a001c3cYkkFWDjXOYn","messageID":"msg_d78ffacd5001xeKarB6UUKKxdR","sessionID":"ses_287007af5ffe4FwON8tsyu2Ogd","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_5ac4cae9392e46cf815077d3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-012 — 会话存储接口定义\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing session storage interface in `pkg/store`.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-012\n10: - **Module**: `pkg/store`\n11: - **Language**: Go\n12: - **Size**: S\n13: - **Base Specs**: \n14:   - `deployment/client-go.md` — Kubernetes client for runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh API\n15:   - `session-store/design.md` — Session store design with Store interface\n16:   - `session-store/spec.md` — Session store specification with requirements\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## Background\n21: \n22: The agentcube system requires a session storage abstraction to persist sandbox metadata keyed by session id. The store module provides a unified interface over Redis and Valkey backends, with support for:\n23: - Session CRUD operations (create, read, update, delete)\n24: - Expiry-based and activity-based session listing for garbage collection\n25: - Index maintenance via sorted sets\n26: - Provider selection via environment variables\n27: - Singleton initialization pattern\n28: \n29: ---\n30: \n31: ## Requirement: Store Interface Contract\n32: \n33: ### Scenario: Store interface provides all required methods\n34: \n35: **GIVEN** a configured Redis or Valkey backend  \n36: **WHEN** the `Store` interface is used  \n37: **THEN** the following methods are available:\n38: - `Ping(ctx context.Context) error` — verifies connectivity\n39: - `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)` — retrieves sandbox by session id\n40: - `StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error` — creates new sandbox record\n41: - `UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error` — updates existing sandbox\n42: - `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error` — removes sandbox\n43: - `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` — lists expired sessions\n44: - `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` — lists inactive sessions\n45: - `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error` — updates last activity timestamp\n46: - `Close() error` — closes the store connection\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ## Requirement: Provider Selection\n51: \n52: ### Scenario: STORE_TYPE selects Redis provider\n53: \n54: **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is set to `\"redis\"` (case-insensitive)  \n55: **WHEN** `Storage()` is called for initialization  \n56: **THEN** Redis implementation is constructed using environment variables `REDIS_ADDR` and `REDIS_PASSWORD`\n57: \n58: ### Scenario: STORE_TYPE selects Valkey provider\n59: \n60: **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is set to `\"valkey\"` (case-insensitive)  \n61: **WHEN** `Storage()` is called for initialization  \n62: **THEN** Valkey implementation is constructed using environment variables `VALKEY_ADDR` and `VALKEY_PASSWORD`\n63: \n64: ### Scenario: Default provider is Redis when STORE_TYPE unset\n65: \n66: **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is not set  \n67: **WHEN** `Storage()` first initializes  \n68: **THEN** Redis implementation is constructed by default\n69: \n70: ### Scenario: Invalid STORE_TYPE fails initialization\n71: \n72: **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is set to an unsupported value (e.g., `\"memcached\"`)  \n73: **WHEN** `Storage()` is called  \n74: **THEN** initialization fails with error indicating unsupported store type\n75: \n76: ---\n77: \n78: ## Requirement: Redis Environment Configuration\n79: \n80: ### Scenario: Redis requires REDIS_ADDR\n81: \n82: **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is `redis` or unset  \n83: **WHEN** Redis store initializes without `REDIS_ADDR` environment variable  \n84: **THEN** initialization fails with error stating REDIS_ADDR is required\n85: \n86: ### Scenario: Redis password required by default\n87: \n88: **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` is set and `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is not `\"false\"`  \n89: **WHEN** `REDIS_PASSWORD` is empty or not set  \n90: **THEN** initialization fails with error stating password is required\n91: \n92: ### Scenario: Redis password optional when explicitly disabled\n93: \n94: **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` is set  \n95: **AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `\"false\"`  \n96: **WHEN** `REDIS_PASSWORD` is empty  \n97: **THEN** initialization succeeds without password\n98: \n99: ---\n100: \n101: ## Requirement: Valkey Environment Configuration\n102: \n103: ### Scenario: Valkey requires VALKEY_ADDR\n104: \n105: **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is `valkey`  \n106: **WHEN** Valkey store initializes without `VALKEY_ADDR` environment variable  \n107: **THEN** initialization fails with error stating VALKEY_ADDR is required\n108: \n109: ### Scenario: Valkey password required by default\n110: \n111: **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is set and `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is not `\"false\"`  \n112: **WHEN** `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is empty or not set  \n113: **THEN** initialization fails with error stating password is required\n114: \n115: ### Scenario: Valkey password optional when explicitly disabled\n116: \n117: **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is set  \n118: **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `\"false\"`  \n119: **WHEN** `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is empty  \n120: **THEN** initialization succeeds without password\n121: \n122: ### Scenario: Valkey DisableCache option from environment\n123: \n124: **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` is set to `\"true\"`  \n125: **WHEN** Valkey client options are built  \n126: **THEN** `DisableCache` is set to `true` on `ClientOption`\n127: \n128: ### Scenario: Valkey ForceSingleClient option from environment\n129: \n130: **GIVEN** `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` is set to `\"true\"`  \n131: **WHEN** Valkey client options are built  \n132: **THEN** `ForceSingleClient` is set to `true` on `ClientOption`\n133: \n134: ---\n135: \n136: ## Requirement: Session Key Naming\n137: \n138: ### Scenario: Session key uses prefix concatenation\n139: \n140: **GIVEN** a session id `abc-123`  \n141: **WHEN** the store writes sandbox data  \n142: **THEN** the string key is `session:abc-123` (prefix `\"session:\"` concatenated with session id)\n143: \n144: ---\n145: \n146: ## Requirement: Ping Connectivity Verification\n147: \n148: ### Scenario: Redis ping returns PONG\n149: \n150: **GIVEN** a healthy Redis server  \n151: **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called on Redis store  \n152: **THEN** the implementation issues PING command  \n153: **AND** expects string response `\"PONG\"`\n154: \n155: ### Scenario: Valkey ping returns PONG\n156: \n157: **GIVEN** a healthy Valkey server  \n158: **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called on Valkey store  \n159: **THEN** the implementation issues `B().Ping()`  \n160: **AND** expects string response `\"PONG\"`\n161: \n162: ---\n163: \n164: ## Requirement: Not Found Semantics\n165: \n166: ### Scenario: Get missing session returns ErrNotFound\n167: \n168: **GIVEN** no key `session:{id}` in backend  \n169: **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID` runs with non-existent session id  \n170: **THEN** error is `ErrNotFound` with message `\"store: not found\"`\n171: \n172: ### Scenario: Redis backend returns Nil for missing key\n173: \n174: **GIVEN** Redis store  \n175: **WHEN** GET command returns Redis `Nil`  \n176: **THEN** `ErrNotFound` is returned\n177: \n178: ### Scenario: Valkey backend returns nil for missing key\n179: \n180: **GIVEN** Valkey store  \n181: **WHEN** GET command returns `IsValkeyNil` true  \n182: **THEN** `ErrNotFound` is returned\n183: \n184: ---\n185: \n186: ## Requirement: StoreSandbox Validation\n187: \n188: ### Scenario: Nil sandbox rejected\n189: \n190: **GIVEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called  \n191: **WHEN** the method executes  \n192: **THEN** error indicates sandbox is nil\n193: \n194: ### Scenario: Zero ExpiresAt rejected\n195: \n196: **GIVEN** `StoreSandbox` is called with sandbox where `ExpiresAt` is zero time  \n197: **WHEN** the method validates input  \n198: **THEN** error indicates invalid expiry\n199: \n200: ---\n201: \n202: ## Requirement: StoreSandbox Atomicity\n203: \n204: ### Scenario: StoreSandbox creates session with all indexes\n205: \n206: **GIVEN** a valid `SandboxInfo` with `SessionID`, `ExpiresAt`, and other fields  \n207: **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called  \n208: **THEN** the operation executes atomically:\n209: - Session key (`session:{id}`) is set with JSON value using SETNX\n210: - `session:expiry` ZSET gets member with score = `ExpiresAt.Unix()`\n211: - `session:last_activity` ZSET gets member with score = `time.Now().Unix()`\n212: \n213: ### Scenario: StoreSandbox fails on any pipeline error\n214: \n215: **GIVEN** Redis/Valkey pipeline/multi operation  \n216: **WHEN** any command in the batch fails  \n217: **THEN** the operation returns error and no partial state is left\n218: \n219: ---\n220: \n221: ## Requirement: UpdateSandbox Semantics\n222: \n223: ### Scenario: UpdateSandbox only modifies session value\n224: \n225: **GIVEN** an existing session with key `session:{id}`  \n226: **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` is called with new sandbox data  \n227: **THEN** only the session JSON value is updated using SET with XX flag  \n228: **AND** expiry and last-activity ZSET entries are NOT modified\n229: \n230: ### Scenario: UpdateSandbox fails on missing key\n231: \n232: **GIVEN** no session key exists for the given session id  \n233: **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` is called  \n234: **THEN** error is returned indicating key does not exist (Redis: SETXX returns false; Valkey: response not \"OK\")\n235: \n236: ---\n237: \n238: ## Requirement: DeleteSandboxBySessionID Cleanup\n239: \n240: ### Scenario: Delete removes session key and both indexes\n241: \n242: **GIVEN** an existing session with data in all three keys  \n243: **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` is called  \n244: **THEN** the operation removes:\n245: - Session key (`session:{id}`) via DEL\n246: - Member from `session:expiry` ZSET via ZREM\n247: - Member from `session:last_activity` ZSET via ZREM\n248: \n249: ### Scenario: Delete executes atomically\n250: \n251: **GIVEN** a valid session id  \n252: **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` runs  \n253: **THEN** all delete operations execute in one pipeline/multi block\n254: \n255: ---\n256: \n257: ## Requirement: ListExpiredSandboxes Operation\n258: \n259: ### Scenario: ListExpired uses ZRANGEBYSCORE on expiry index\n260: \n261: **GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` with limit > 0  \n262: **WHEN** the implementation queries the index  \n263: **THEN** it selects members from `session:expiry` with scores from negative infinity to `before.Unix()`  \n264: **AND** limited to `limit` entries\n265: \n266: ### Scenario: ListExpired with limit <= 0 returns nil\n267: \n268: **GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes` called with limit <= 0  \n269: **WHEN** executed  \n270: **THEN** returns `nil, nil`\n271: \n272: ### Scenario: ListExpired loads JSON for each session id\n273: \n274: **GIVEN** ZRANGEBYSCORE returns session ids  \n275: **WHEN** fetching sandbox data  \n276: **THEN** each id is used to GET the corresponding `session:{id}` key  \n277: **AND** JSON is unmarshaled to `SandboxInfo`\n278: \n279: ---\n280: \n281: ## Requirement: ListInactiveSandboxes Operation\n282: \n283: ### Scenario: ListInactive uses ZRANGEBYSCORE on last_activity index\n284: \n285: **GIVEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` with limit > 0  \n286: **WHEN** the implementation queries the index  \n287: **THEN** it selects members from `session:last_activity` with scores ≤ `before.Unix()`  \n288: **AND** limited to `limit` entries\n289: \n290: ### Scenario: ListInactive with limit <= 0 returns nil\n291: \n292: **GIVEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes` called with limit <= 0  \n293: **WHEN** executed  \n294: **THEN** returns `nil, nil`\n295: \n296: ---\n297: \n298: ## Requirement: List Operations Tolerate Missing Keys\n299: \n300: ### Scenario: Orphan ZSET member is skipped\n301: \n302: **GIVEN** a session id returned from ZSET but without corresponding string value  \n303: **WHEN** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` runs  \n304: **THEN** that id is omitted from the returned slice  \n305: **AND** the operation does not fail for the whole batch\n306: \n307: ---\n308: \n309: ## Requirement: UpdateSessionLastActivity Preconditions\n310: \n311: ### Scenario: Empty session id rejected\n312: \n313: **GIVEN** empty session id  \n314: **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called  \n315: **THEN** error is returned\n316: \n317: ### Scenario: Zero time uses current time\n318: \n319: **GIVEN** an existing session  \n320: **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called with zero time  \n321: **THEN** `time.Now()` is used as the activity timestamp\n322: \n323: ### Scenario: Non-zero time uses provided value\n324: \n325: **GIVEN** an existing session  \n326: **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called with non-zero `at` timestamp  \n327: **THEN** the provided timestamp is used as the activity score in ZADD\n328: \n329: ### Scenario: UpdateSessionLastActivity requires existing session\n330: \n331: **GIVEN** no `session:{id}` key exists  \n332: **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called  \n333: **THEN** error is `ErrNotFound`\n334: \n335: ---\n336: \n337: ## Requirement: Singleton Initialization\n338: \n339: ### Scenario: Storage returns singleton instance\n340: \n341: **GIVEN** `Storage()` is called multiple times  \n342: **WHEN** after first initialization  \n343: **THEN** the same store instance is returned every time\n344: \n345: ### Scenario: Concurrent Storage calls initialize once\n346: \n347: **GIVEN** multiple goroutines call `Storage()` concurrently  \n348: **WHEN** they execute concurrently  \n349: **THEN** `initStore` executes exactly once via `sync.Once`\n350: \n351: ### Scenario: Init failure triggers fatal log\n352: \n353: **GIVEN** store initialization fails  \n354: **WHEN** `Storage()` is called  \n355: **THEN** `klog.Fatalf` is called with error message\n356: \n357: ---\n358: \n359: ## Requirement: Redis and Valkey Equivalence\n360: \n361: ### Scenario: Both backends implement same interface\n362: \n363: **GIVEN** Redis and Valkey stores with equivalent configuration  \n364: **WHEN** equivalent operations are performed  \n365: **THEN** both backends produce identical results for:\n366: - Session CRUD operations\n367: - Listing expired/inactive sessions\n368: - Last activity updates\n369: - Error semantics (`ErrNotFound`)\n370: \n371: ---\n372: \n373: ## Acceptance Criteria\n374: \n375: - [ ] Store interface defined in `pkg/store/store.go`\n376: - [ ] ErrNotFound error defined and returned for missing sessions\n377: - [ ] Redis implementation in `pkg/store/store_redis.go`\n378: - [ ] Valkey implementation in `pkg/store/store_valkey.go`\n379: - [ ] Singleton pattern in `pkg/store/singleton.go` with `Storage()` function\n380: - [ ] Environment variables parsed correctly for both providers\n381: - [ ] Password policy enforced (required by default, optional when disabled)\n382: - [ ] Session key naming uses `session:` prefix\n383: - [ ] Expiry index maintained via `session:expiry` ZSET\n384: - [ ] Last activity index maintained via `session:last_activity` ZSET\n385: - [ ] Atomic operations for Store, Update, Delete\n386: - [ ] List operations with limit <= 0 return nil\n387: - [ ] Orphan ZSET members handled gracefully\n388: - [ ] All acceptance scenarios pass verification\n389: \n390: ---\n391: \n392: ## References\n393: \n394: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md`\n395: - Base Spec: `deployment/client-go.md`\n396: - Base Spec: `session-store/design.md`\n397: - Base Spec: `session-store/spec.md`\n\n(End of file - total 397 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-012 — 会话存储接口定义\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing session storage interface in `pkg/store`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-012\n- **Module**: `pkg/store`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: S\n- **Base Specs**: \n  - `deployment/client-go.md` — Kubernetes client for runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh API\n  - `session-store/design.md` — Session store design with Store interface\n  - `session-store/spec.md` — Session store specification with requirements\n\n---\n\n## Background","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775851522232,"end":1775851522249}}}}
